      "comment_id" : 78883191,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Not quite complete: you still can use <code>y |= expr</code> with booleans and it gives the same result on <code>y</code> as your variants with the important note that <b>it is not short-curtuit</b>, meaning that expr is always evaluated, even in case of <code>y==true</code>"
    }, {
