      "comment_id" : 78884038,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "And, having this in mind,  <i>in your case</i> with <code>hasChanges</code> it would <i>probably</i> be better to prefer <code>y=y||x</code> form to benefit from short-ciruit, because when you found any change it is not actually needed to do susequent diffs because you already know the answer. (Especially important in real life situation when compared objects are complicated and <code>diff</code>ing them them is not quite fast)"
